	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You strike a piece of iron, creating a spark. The piece of iron you struck rapidly grows hot as you chant an incantation. At the same time, a metal item you can see grows just as hot, making it hard to wield if held or worn by a creature.</em></p><p>You can heat a metal weapon or armor, a 5 ft. square of metal flooring or walls, or any other metal object equal in size or smaller than a suit of plate mail. Any creature in physical contact with the heated object must make a constitution save.</p><p><strong>[[/save constitution]]{Constitution Save}</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes [[/damage 2d6 fire]] damage.* The target can drop the object, but if they don't or can't, they have disadvantage on attack rolls and skill checks for 1 round.</p></li><li><p><strong>Success:</strong> Half damage.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p><strong>Concentration:</strong> Once on each subsequent turn, you can heat the metal object again as a bonus action.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> Increase damage by [[/damage 1d6 fire]] for each spell level above 2nd.</p>",
			"chat": ""
		},
